 to the substantial literature on the occupation, serves as a case study in foreign policy analysis, and tells a surprising new story about World War II.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aJapanologistszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aPolicy scienceszUnited Statesy20th century. 0aPostwar reconstructionzJapanxPlanning. 4aAsian Studies. 4aMilitary History. 4aU.S. History.  apostwar Japan, US foreign policy, policymaking, postwar planning, US-led occupation of postwar Japan, occupation history, Washington's postwar liberal internationalism, foreign policy analysis, World War II.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066587108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2017z9783110547764oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150170784140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501707841423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501707841/original  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  a978-3-11-066587-1  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2017  aZDB-23-DGGb2017